---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Research - Ayush Shahi"
  description="Research by Ayush Shahi on development economics, labor markets, and inequality"
  currentPage="research"
>
  <h2 class="section-header">Academic Work (Undergraduate)</h2>

  <ul class="paper-list">
    <li class="paper-entry">
      <h3 class="paper-title">
        Culture, Institutions, and the Child Penalty
        <span class="paper-links">
          <a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1SdXiOslsPe4ifloB9L7ydZ6-s0GbTOm3/view?usp=sharing" target="_blank" rel="noopener">[PDF]</a>
        </span>
      </h3>
      <p class="paper-venue">Capstone Thesis, Department of Economics, Ashoka University</p>
      <button class="abstract-toggle" onclick="toggleAbstract('abstract-1')">
        <span class="arrow">&#9660;</span> Abstract
      </button>
      <div id="abstract-1" class="abstract-content">
        <p>
          This thesis examines gender norms, work-family policies, and the motherhood penalty in developing nations.
          Using data from Demographic and Health Surveys, the study employs instrumental variable analysis and a
          staggered difference-in-differences approach to investigate how cultural and institutional factors
          shape the economic costs of parenthood, with particular focus on mothers in developing economies.
        </p>
      </div>
    </li>

    <li class="paper-entry">
      <h3 class="paper-title">
        Can Digital Payment Adoption Reduce Crime?
        <span class="paper-links">
          <a href="https://www.ramjaseconomicreview.com/_files/ugd/535c7d_ff329409c84347cdbc67f62d66b0028f.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener">[PDF]</a>
        </span>
      </h3>
      <p class="paper-authors">With Hiba Hasan and Sahil Garud</p>
      <p class="paper-venue">Ramjas Economic Review, Vol. 7(1), pp. 1-10</p>
      <p class="paper-award">Best Research Paper, 23rd Annual Winter Conference</p>
      <button class="abstract-toggle" onclick="toggleAbstract('abstract-2')">
        <span class="arrow">&#9660;</span> Abstract
      </button>
      <div id="abstract-2" class="abstract-content">
        <p>
          This paper examines the relationship between Unified Payments Interface (UPI) adoption and economic crime
          in Indian districts. We investigate whether the shift toward digital payments reduces opportunities for
          certain types of crime by altering the transaction landscape and reducing the prevalence of cash-based exchanges.
        </p>
      </div>
    </li>

    <li class="paper-entry">
      <h3 class="paper-title">
        Can Orphanhood Explain Nutritional Disparities?
        <span class="paper-links">
          <a href="https://www.hansrajcollege.ac.in/uploads/researchinnovation/callforpapersposter/issue1_vol3/Paper%202.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener">[PDF]</a>
        </span>
      </h3>
      <p class="paper-authors">With Rishika Jain</p>
      <p class="paper-venue">HRC Journal of Economics and Finance, Vol. 3(1), pp. 25-47</p>
      <p class="paper-award">Best Research Paper, 22nd Annual Winter Conference</p>
      <button class="abstract-toggle" onclick="toggleAbstract('abstract-3')">
        <span class="arrow">&#9660;</span> Abstract
      </button>
      <div id="abstract-3" class="abstract-content">
        <p>
          This study provides a comparative analysis of health outcomes using National Family Health Survey Round 5 data.
          We examine whether orphanhood status can explain observed nutritional disparities among children in India,
          controlling for household characteristics and regional factors.
        </p>
      </div>
    </li>

    <li class="paper-entry">
      <h3 class="paper-title">
        Ctrl+Aid+Delete: Regime-Contingent Effects of Foreign Aid
        <span class="paper-links">
          <a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1G4L_AVA1Oks2LqnCh78jXV4VUsWlDAvn/view?usp=sharing" target="_blank" rel="noopener">[PDF]</a>
        </span>
      </h3>
      <button class="abstract-toggle" onclick="toggleAbstract('abstract-4')">
        <span class="arrow">&#9660;</span> Abstract
      </button>
      <div id="abstract-4" class="abstract-content">
        <p>
          This paper investigates how internet-related foreign aid affects government capacity to control the internet.
          The study explores the contingent effects of aid depending on regime type and governance structures,
          examining the unintended consequences of technology-focused development assistance.
        </p>
      </div>
    </li>
  </ul>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .paper-list {
    list-style: disc;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .paper-list .paper-entry {
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-lg);
    padding-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .paper-list .paper-entry::marker {
    color: var(--color-text);
  }
</style>

<script is:inline>
  function toggleAbstract(abstractId) {
    const abstract = document.getElementById(abstractId);
    const button = abstract.previousElementSibling;

    abstract.classList.toggle('open');
    button.classList.toggle('open');
  }
</script>
